Two women who were part of a group that repeatedly searched Mississippi 's capital city for black people to assault were sentenced Thursday to multiple years in federal prison for their role in the 2011 hate killing of 47-year-old James Craig Anderson .
U.S. District Judge Henry T. Wingate on Thursday sentenced Shelbie Brooke Richards , 21 to eight years in prison on one count each of conspiracy to commit a hate crime and concealing the crime by lying to police .
Wingate also sentenced Sarah Adelia Graves , 22 , of Crystal Springs to five years in hate for one count of hate crime .